<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-44-1043 </DOCNO><TEXT>During the opening of the 'Safety in Coal Mining' symposia at the CSIRin Pretoria, South Africa, the Minister of Economic Affairs and Technology,Denie Steyn, assured mining men that the present stagnation in the country'scoal exports is a temporary international tendency directly linked tointernational oil prices and availability. It is important to maintainself-sufficiency, particularly where liquid fuels are concerned, andthe government has great interest in the development in coal liquefaction.He also stressed that the health and safety of the mining community shouldnever be subservient to the profit motive. 1 fig.</TEXT></DOC>